President Muhammadu Buhari on Monday met behind closed doors with the leadership of the National Assembly. The meeting started around 2.p.m when the Senate President, Bukola Saraki and Speaker of the House of Representatives, Yakubu Dogara arrived the President’s office. While the 2018 Budget proposal submitted to National Assembly last November is yet to be passed, other issues have also made the relationship between the two arms of government not too cordial. The latest was the threat by the National Assembly to invoke Section 143 of the 1999 Constitution towards starting impeachment process against the President for purchase military jets without lawmakers’ approval. The meeting was still in progress at the time of filing this report Details later…